name: STEPHANIE CEMO

social_posts.post_text:
Pro Rally Driver and Hoonigan Founder Ken Block Killed in Snowmobile Accident. 

What a massive loss in the motorsports community. I always looked up to Ken. Senseless tragedy, but man did he live 1000x more than most. 

Rest easy @kblock43 😭 #legend

As many of you… I’m still in utter shock over the sudden passing of Ken Block. Most don’t ask how a driver selects their car number, but for me… I selected #43 in honor of Ken 10 years ago after I had the opportunity to meet him in 2012, thanks to @joshkalis. After that night in Vegas, I always looked up to his fearlessness… his kindness and watching him tackle his dreams as a driver even as he started his driving career at an older age than most. He got to do what he loved and had such a zest for life and accomplishing new things. He truly lived a life of meaning, courage and broke down every barrier in his path. I sat up late last night thinking about his family and the ones closest to him, I cannot imagine the pain they’re feeling. My heart goes out to all of them. 

Legends never die… Godspeed @kblock43. #43VER
.
Video credit @carphysics

I just had to post the newest piece of art that arrived today. I am a firm believer that art creates the soul of a home and this piece is pure magic. I really wanted to just post the artist, @yoakimbelanger, because more people need to know about this man. What a beautiful mind! Go to his page to see the video of it being made. 
.
The colors… that it’s on polished stainless steel… the texture and that calming gaze from the subject stole my heart not even seeing it in person. But in person, it’s even more magnetic. 
.
Thanks to @galerieleroyer in Canada for getting it here safely and obviously… thank you Yoakim for creating my favorite piece so far. I will forever cherish it and know that it will fill my heart with the best vibes for years to come. 🙌🏼❤️
.
#visualart #art #yoakimbelanger

Sorry for my absence for the last several months. My brother and I have really been going through one. We lost my dad unexpectedly on Christmas Day. This guy’s energy lit up and commanded every room he walked into. Im still pretty numb, as we have a lot on our hands with my mom and her care… I have have felt glimpses of the emptiness over the last few days that I will never see him again. He gave so much to so many and what he left behind will be his legacy. We miss him immensely. RIP Dad…. As he always said to me when he was done with our phone calls… “let me get out of your hair”… I love you, I was a lucky girl. ❤️‍🩹
